Spend a relaxing 30 minutes with me, voice actress Azuki Miho
Spend a relaxing 30 minutes with me, voice actress Azuki Miho
Looks like you will be able to wrap up PCP's elementary school arc in the next two issues.
It is only temporary, but you will have the weekly PCP, the PCP for Hisshou,
and a third work, Reversi, all going on at the same time.
and I have a week between the final weekly PCP and the first Reversi.
That is a lot of time.
When I wrote down a schedule for working on them together in the future,
I noticed that Reversi will have four chapters of 19 pages each, or 76 pages in total.
That will amount to 121 pages a month, or 30 pages a week.
Will not that be pretty rough?
We will do just fine if I do not take any time off.
Shuujin, from now on you are going to be doing more pages too,
so keep up the quality of your scripts, okay?
I am not cut out for manual labor.
Mashiro, shall I place the toner over here?
When you have four desks, this is the best way to arrange them.
All we did was rearrange things, but it feels like a whole new room.
I wanted to maximize the limited space we have here.
I call dibs on the desk nearest to Mashiro!
In that case, I will be taking this one, I guess.
Who the heck is this guy?
He just barged in here in and took over.
I know he is been an assistant here before, but...
We have been here longer than him.
If you have drawn up a schedule already, could you please show it to me?
It will be something like this.
I think I can manage it somehow.
Oh, I meant for the assistants.
So far, I have always had them come in on Tuesday, and we usually finish by Thursday.
But from now on, I might need them full time until Friday.
Friday's not very good for me...
I am completely okay with that!
This job was originally supposed to take until Friday anyway.
And also, until I finish Reversi's first chapter,
I was hoping some of you could work on Saturdays, too.
You should have said that beforehand.
I will be here on Saturdays!
Even though I am working on my own manga.
That would be a great help!
In that case, we should be able to manage it.
Um, who is the chief around here?
Uh, we do not really have one.
If you are going to work on two manga without selecting a chief to manage things,
you will not be able to control the workflow.
Then, Ogawa, will you be the chief?
We are counting on you, Ogawa!
Our efficiency has really shot through the roof since you came, Ogawa!
And our overall quality has increased as well.
Ogawa, please keep teaching me more things.
You are lagging behind a bit.
Since PCP's jumped to a middle school setting now,
I have gotten caught up in redrawing all the scenery and characters.
We have a chief now, so we can make up for lost time!
Minor delays are popping up here and there,
but Reversi got more votes than Zombie Gun as a one-shot!
I do not want to lose to him in our serialized chapters either!
Things are not looking good at this rate.
You need to have 26 pages of PCP ready in three days for Hisshou.
we will need 41 more pages to meet the deadline for Reversi's first chapter.
That is 67 pages in one week!
Why did not you tell me, Saikou?
But there is no point in calculating how much is left.
I just have to keep drawing!
I will not let the quality drop either.
If I do not sleep from now until then, I can get it done!
That is six days without sleep!
And I have gotten used to drawing the separate styles of PCP and Reversi.
Even if Mashiro does finish inking,
we still do not have nearly enough assistants.
Starting on Friday, when I cannot come in to work...
The trains are about to stop, so that will be all for today.
I will try to get as much done as I can tonight.
I will stay until the first train.
Until I have caught up on finishing the manuscripts that Mashiro has inked already.
If Mashiro is not going to stop...
Then, I will come as early as I can tomorrow.
Yes, I am coming home now.
Have you all been working through the night?
My wife and I will apply blacks, whites, and tones.
If you need any, give us the pages!
even though the deadline is tomorrow!
Mashiro, at this rate, you will not finish Reversi!
We can handle the backgrounds and minor characters,
so you just concentrate on inking in the main characters.
Everyone, if you have a panel with backgrounds, cut it out and give it to me!
Give the ones with background characters to Orihara.
Do the same with each page...
You should all go home and rest.
I am going to stay here until it is done.
Going home and coming back would just waste time.
But then, we will be less efficient...
Efficiency does not mean anything anymore.
We are finishing pages as soon as Mashiro's done with them,
but they are still slowly piling up.
Mashiro, even if you finish PCP on time tomorrow,
you cannot possibly finish Reversi in three days
Chief, you think we will not be able to pull this off.
Then why are you the only one going home?!
Moriya, this is all my fault for being late with the manuscript.
If you are upset, then bring it up with me.
Is not Ogawa being a little unfair to the rest of us?
Just because he has two jobs...
No, that is what it means to be a professional assistant.
If he pulled an all-nighter here, he would be inconveniencing another manga artist.
But it still hurts to have someone as capable as Ogawa leave.
He does do his work well, and can get twice as much done as any of us.
Who could that be this late at night?
Even if I manage to finish inking by tomorrow afternoon,
I do not have enough assistants to finish in time.
I found two more people to help you out during the evenings.
I will do whatever you need, as long as you pay me the assistant's wage, that is.
I have been trying to get together a few of my more skilled colleagues since yesterday, and I finally found some.
As the chief, I have a responsibility to get these manuscripts done.
Um, we are out of desks here.
Guess I will work in the kitchen.
I will take the bathroom, then.
And just this time, I will come straight here in the evenings after my other job finishes.
Let us give it one more push!
I was a bit worried this time,
but I guess when it comes to you two, I do not need to worry about missing deadlines.
No, it was actually really close.
This time around, it was all thanks to the hard work of our assistants.
If you can get past something like this, then you will be all right.
Now, take a look at this.
It is the sample copy of Monday's issue.
Does not this sort of count as double protagonists, too?
It is a bit different, but Niizuma understands very well.
He understands just how important the antagonist is in a standard battle manga.
But, in terms of relationships between rivals,
the one between Reversi's black demon Schwarz and white demon Weiss is better.
Eiji, I was not expecting you to respond like this.
First place by far and away!
Come on, Niizuma, cannot you get even a little bit excited?
That is this week's sample copy.
Well, I do not think it can reach your 767 votes, though.
What rank did we get in the final results?
We got first place by a huge lead!
It is all because of you!
How many votes did we get?
Last week, Zombie Gun got 767 votes.
But, the real challenge starts now!
You are in first place again this week.
That is three weeks in a row!
And this week, we have a 40 vote gap between us and Zombie Gun in second place!
You have won three weeks in a row against Niizuma!
Winning against that Eiji, three weeks in row?
No, it cannot be this easy.
Let us keep on getting first place!
Ever since their new series started,
Ashirogi and Master Niizuma have been hogging the top two spots!
It is not a rank to be depressed over.
If it were not for Zombie Gun and Reversi, you would be in about third place now.
I am just in shock that Yuri's What God Gave Me is in 17th place!
Ashirogi Mutou is an amazing manga author,
but Azuki Miho's an amazing voice actress, too!
Why did you bring her up all of a sudden?
I knew Miho would not tell anybody.
She is on the front cover!
She is on a roll now because her role as Ai in Impromptu 12 is so popular.
Sh-She said she wanted to stay out of public eye, though.
She still does not want to appear on TV, but magazines and radio are okay.
She said she has a show starting soon.
She really has not told you anything yet, has she?
She should have, no matter how embarrassed she is...
Things are going swimmingly for both Mashiro and Azuki, though.
The wedding cannot be that far off!
Well, at this rate, it feels like things are going too well...
You are the one who always had complete confidence in Reversi.
Try and go for four weeks in first place!
What is it, all of a sudden?
I thought it would be faster to show you this in person rather than explain it over the phone.
It is next week's sample copy.
And he killed the previous rival off like it was nothing!
Having Chapters 2 and 3 in second place is not bad at all.
But despite that, he cast away this character.
He knows how important the antagonist is in standard battle manga.
If the enemy is not received well, you swap him out.
It is a basic rule of battle manga.
It is not like it got any negative feedback, though.
It is most likely a knee-jerk reaction to seeing the first chapter of Reversi.
It is to steal first place from you.
That his antagonist was weaker than Reversi's.
But it took a long time of trial and error to create our double protagonists.
We cannot easily swap them out for new ones like Eiji can.
Zombie Gun is in first with 472 votes.
So we lost to GIRI, too.
Why did our vote count suddenly drop so much?
When Eiji swapped out his enemy character, I felt it myself.
The readers may have realized it as well.
The fundamental premise of Reversi is having two enemies and rivals: our double protagonists.
We cannot use the basic rule of battle manga Hattori talked about,
which is swapping out enemies if they become unpopular.
We have to take the confrontation between Schwarz and Weiss all the way until the end.
We may need to further discuss this at some point.
But for now, focus continuing the story in a way that best utilizes this premise.
How far can I take these two?
How long will it remain interesting?
You texted Azuki and told her that her role in our anime would be her greatest ever, right?
How many volumes of Impromptu 12 are there?
It is a popular manga that is been serialized for eight years already.
That is how long I will have to keep this going.
I will have to make this a manga that will not lose to Niizuma Eiji and Zombie Gun.
And one that will become an anime.
In any case, I have to make this last as long as possible with just Schwarz and Weiss.
So that Reversi becomes a flagship series, for Saikou and Azuki's sake!
There is a lot of fighting in this one.
It is a standard battle manga, after all.
With this, you can draw battle scenes to your heart's content, right?
Well then, go ahead and make a clean storyboard.
Well, it just started, so I think it is a bit early to think about changing the setting yet.
We cannot alter our premise of having two protagonists,
so even if it drops a little bit, we have no choice but to continue.
I have already finished the storyboard for Chapter 9, if you want to take a look.
It is well done, but it feels a bit thin.
So far, the chapters have been rich in content, and the story progressed quickly.
Chapter 9 is clearly much slower, though.
It is not bad to have a chapter centered on battles,
but in the end, Takagi's strengths lie in psychological warfare and tactics.
Uh, well, if I pushed their confrontation along, the series would get a lot shorter.
Hattori, you said before that we have to make this manga a mainstay of Jack, right?
A mainstay is a flagship series, right?
When we talk about Jack flagships,
Dragonball, One Piece, and Naruto come to mind.
Works with a long duration that sell more than a million copies!
There is no doubt that the manga you have spoken of are flagships.
even you said that you wanted it gain flagship status, an anime, and a long run!
I never said I wanted it to have a long run.
I did say I wanted the first two things, though.
Th-Then, are you okay with it ending before Zombie Gun?!
If it is good, then I am fine with that.
The ideal would be to maintain popularity over a long run, but...
A manga that runs through all its content at once is fine, too.
If you develop the conflict between Schwarz and Weiss in a way that plays to your strengths,
then I do not think this series will last very long.
However, the length of our run is not important.
It is the quality of our work.
Remember why we wanted to do Reversi as a weekly series?
It is because we are trying to get the top spot in Weekly Shounen Jack, right?
Let us aim for the top, dash forward, and come up with the best possible ending.
I know that you... that Reversi, can do it.
If that means it will be short, then so be it.
Um, tonight is my first show, so I am pretty nervous.
Well then, let me jump right into it.
Sorry, but do you have a minute?
It is really okay if Reversi does not last long, right?
Then, I have got to spit this out.
I have pretty much decided already how the conflict between Schwarz and Weiss will end.
And after their confrontation is over, I do not want to pull out a new enemy.
Reversi is not that kind of manga.
If we resolve that conflict in the most interesting way I can think of,
and execute it in one go without letting the readers catch their breath,
it will not last more than one or two years...
No, it will probably only top out at 50 chapters.
Just write whatever you think is most interesting,
and we will end it the way you want to.
If you write Reversi like that,
it will definitely become a masterpiece.
It may be short, but if people acknowledge it,
Do you think it will get an anime?
And if it does not have the best role for Azuki, I will be upset.
This may be the first time I have ever asked this of you,
but, for me and Azuki, and also for you, please turn this into a masterpiece.
I am counting on you, Shuujin!
I will write without wasting a single word!
We do not need any unnecessary elements!
I will draw it with all I have!
All right, let us forge ahead!
Drawn Out and All at Once
This will be the day I propose to Yuri!
I will make sure you are happy!
I will do anything to get it.
As soon as I reach my goals, it all falls through again
We met after such a long time
Has the mood changed for us?
It seemed like more fun back then
Do not stop screaming, do not stop struggling
You have done enough for others
I still, still have something I have not told you yet
Beyond each of my dreams lies yet another dream
Whenever I am close to fulfilling my goals, all effort becomes fruitless
We walk ahead, hold each other, and with little things
we support each other to reach what we promised
When we lack confidence, we put a hand to our heart
and reread the pages we assembled into a story
They lead up to today and continue into the morrow
until the day that our dreams come true
